AI and automated data-use restrictions

You may not use the software, source code, documentation, designs, data, commit
history, issues, pull requests, discussions, or any other repository content:

1. To train, fine-tune, improve, evaluate, benchmark, validate, or test any
   artificial intelligence, machine learning, large language model, foundation
   model, embedding model, code-generation system, retrieval system, or related
   automated system.
2. As part of any dataset, corpus, index, vector database, embedding store,
   knowledge base, benchmark, model input collection, or model output
   evaluation set.
3. For automated scraping, crawling, harvesting, mirroring, bulk downloading,
   indexing, or extraction, except as strictly necessary for ordinary source
   control operations by a human user or for security scanning performed on
   Steeple's behalf.
4. To generate or assist in generating substantially similar software,
   documentation, product designs, business materials, listings, or data.

